name: Air Jordan 7 Retro "Raptor"
description: This is the Air Jordan VII (7) Retro "Raptors" for 2012. The "Raptors" color way is one of the most coveted AJ VII (7) designs. Although popularly dubbed the "Raptors" because of the similarity to Toronto's uniforms it is actually the shoe MJ wore during the 1992 playoffs as he knocked off the Knicks, swept a good Heat team, destroyed the Cavs, and beat the Blazers for his second ring. He also set a historic mark by scoring 35 points in a half during the Finals and after hitting 6 three pointers he gave "The Shrug" as he passed by the scorers table.

name: Air Jordan 7 "Olympic"
description: This is the Air Jordan VII (7) Retro Olympic released in 2012. For this years 2012 Summer Olympics Nike and Jordan Brand have hit us with all the classic retro releases themed around the Olympics games. This year is the 20th anniversary of the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona where the USA basketball team ("Dream Team") took the gold and stunned the world bringing the game of basketball to new heights. It was only right that JB re-retro this iconic model that MJ sported during those Olympics. These shoes sold out within minutes and are increasingly harder to find. Be sure to add this gem to your collection.

name: Air Jordan 9 "Bentley Ellis" (Crawfish)
description: This is the Air Jordan IX (9) "Bentley Ellis" edition. This Fall Jordan Brand is bringing back the AJ IX (9) with a vengeance dropping six new color ways that are all a part of the "Johnny Kilroy Pack". As most of you know after the 1992-1993 NBA season Michael Jordan retired from the game of basketball to follow his childhood dream of playing professional baseball. While he was away the Air Jordan line continued with the AJ IX (9) which he never wore on the hardwood. As legend goes (or Nike commercials at the time) multiple players were seen playing in independent leagues all over the country who shadowed MJ's game, performing Jumpman style dunks, switch hand layups, buzzer beaters and fade away shots. It was believed that these players were in fact MJ himself taking on alter-egos to fulfill his ongoing desire to play the game. One of these identities, named "Bentley Ellis", played for a semi-pro team called the "Crawfish" who sport a Cleveland Cavs-like color way. These shoes were very limited so be sure to add it to your collection now.

name: Air Jordan 9 Retro "Johnny Kilroy"
description: This is the Air Jordan IX (9) Retro "Johnny Kilroy" edition. This Fall Jordan Brand is bringing back the AJ IX (9) with a vengeance dropping six new color ways that are all a part of the "Johnny Kilroy Pack". As most of you know after the 1992-1993 NBA season Michael Jordan retired from the game of basketball to follow his childhood dream of playing professional baseball. While he was away the Air Jordan line continued with the AJ IX (9) which he never wore on the hardwood. As legend goes (or Nike commercials at the time) multiple players were seen playing in independent leagues all over the country who shadowed MJ's game, performing Jumpman style dunks, switch hand layups, buzzer beaters and fade away shots. It was believed that these players were in fact MJ himself taking on alter-egos to fulfill his ongoing desire to play the game. One of these identities, named "Johnny Kilroy", actually played in the NBA for the Chicago Bulls and wore the number 4. This is a Air Jordan IX (9) "Johnny Kilroy" player exclusive edition that bears the number "4" on the heel and the inner tongue reads "Kilroy Kicks Butt".

description: This is the Nike Air Foamposite Pro "Gym Green" that has been anticipated since release info was first revealed in January of this year.
